{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"26fdad92-cfcd-43dc-8622-b71a6462487f","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` to automatically re-run tests whenever you save a file:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThe `--filter` flag scopes it to just your failing test for faster feedback. When you save `InventoryServiceTests.cs`, the test re-runs automatically.\n\n**The bug:** `RemoveStock` subtracts without checking if there's enough stock. It needs a guard:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException(\"Insufficient stock\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWant me to apply the fix so you can see it pass with watch mode?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"87992313-d390-4291-999c-a9efdb1d70da","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up hot reload for rapid iteration. With `dotnet watch`, they can re-run tests automatically on file changes. Since the project uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (via global.json config), they can use `dotnet test --watch` or `dotnet watch test`.\n\nLet me give them the command to use.","outputTokens":294,"requestId":"BD0F:2586A7:1C8661A:20075E0:6A07BF6C"},"id":"8c1ede50-070f-4309-8d2a-0614a56bd057","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:51:00.447Z","parentId":"b8557fda-187b-4559-831b-3bd7e86caf89"}
